<br>
It reminds me of a couple years ago when the Dodgers (a professional baseball team here Didi and other visitors to Los Angeles) had &quot;one African-American&quot; on their team!! Oh the horror!! The team that had broken segregation in the major leagues had only one African-American player! the media was all up in arms, because the three Dominicans and one Puerto Rican they had didn't count as they were merely &quot;black&quot;. Cause when they enter the high end dept store, they aren't closely watched, or get profiled by police and pulled over..cause they aren't African-American (black) they are Dominican!! See that clears it all up!! Cripes.<br>
<br>
