<br>
What I am is Scottish. Not British, welsh, irish, and especially not english. <br>
<br>
I like Bag pipe music, haggis, caiber tossing, and wearing Kilts. I like big ass Claymores, William Wallace, and old castles. I was taught to head butt at age 2. I drank bear at age 1. <br>
<br>
Moved to Canada when I was 3, took about till I was 10 to loose the accent. I remember when I was 19 I went to this bar, Black guy came up to me after he saw me glance his way, no I wasn't lookin at him, he just happened to be sitting near the pool table my buddy was playing. Anyway he comes up and says &quot;What you stareing at whitey.&quot; I got up look im in the eyes and said &quot;First off I'm not white, I'm scottish, Secondly I am trying to watch my friend play pool.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then he was like &quot;Kewl, your from Britain?&quot; I said, &quot;No way man Scotland&quot;<br>
<br>
Anyways he ended up buying me a bear, we had a few laughs. Started joking around about stuff. <br>
<br>
I never once saw this guy as Black, I saw him as a Canadian, And nowadays if you ask me what I am I say Scottish-Canadian. I was born Scottish, and my heart and soul is Scottish.....But at the same time &quot;I AM CANADIAN&quot;<br>
<br>
